{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-markdown-remark-js","path":"/common/common/docs/add_repo.md","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Operate First"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"fa82f28f-dd71-5988-8b66-99be9279fe02","html":"<h2 id=\"adding-a-repo\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#adding-a-repo\" aria-label=\"adding a repo permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Adding a Repo</h2>\n<p>All Operate First GitHub repositories are stored declaratively in the <code class=\"language-text\">github-config.yaml</code> file. To add a new repo we\nneed to update this file, and then our <a href=\"https://github.com/kubernetes/test-infra/tree/master/prow/cmd/peribolos\">Peribolos</a> deployment will bring these changes live.</p>\n<p>Follow the steps outlined below to add your repo:</p>\n<ol class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Fork/Clone the <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/common\">common repo</a>.</li>\n<li>Open <code class=\"language-text\">common/github-config.yaml</code> in a file editor.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add your new repo to <code class=\"language-text\">orgs.operate-first.repos</code> by appending this list, use the following template:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"yaml\"><pre class=\"language-yaml\"><code class=\"language-yaml\"><span class=\"token key atrule\">&lt;repo-name></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">description</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> &lt;repo<span class=\"token punctuation\">-</span>description<span class=\"token punctuation\">></span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">has_projects</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean important\">false</span>\n<span class=\"token key atrule\">auto_init</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean important\">true</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Fill in the values encapsulated in<code class=\"language-text\">&lt;&gt;</code> as follows:</p>\n</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;repo-name&gt;</code>: Name of the GitHub repo</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">&lt;repo-description</code>: Short repo description (this will appear at the top of the repo).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can find a full list of available parameters <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/github-ae@latest/rest/reference/repos#create-an-organization-repository\">here</a>.</p>\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"pf-c-list\">\n<li>Before you commit your changes, you will also need to add a team to the <code class=\"language-text\">github-config.yaml</code>. You can add a team by following step 3 of <a href=\"add_gh_member_and_access.md#Create-a-GitHub-Team\">these instructions</a>.</li>\n<li>Commit your changes and make a <a href=\"https://github.com/operate-first/apps/blob/master/contributing.md#creating-pull-requests\">pull request</a>. This should only require 1 commit.</li>\n</ol>","fields":{"srcLink":"https://github.com/operate-first/common/blob/master/docs/add_repo.md"},"frontmatter":{"title":"","description":null,"extraClasses":null,"banner":null}}},"pageContext":{"id":"fa82f28f-dd71-5988-8b66-99be9279fe02"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1764348645","2823140819","3000541721","3606484676"]}